## Think Critically

:::evaluate{criteria="instruction-set-design"}

### Why only two instruction types?

The Hack instruction set has just A-instructions and C-instructions, far fewer than a modern x86 or ARM CPU. What are the advantages and disadvantages of a minimal instruction set?

### Criteria
- Identifies simplicity / ease of implementation benefits
- Considers code density and program size trade-offs
- Recognizes that a minimal ISA makes the assembler and compiler easier to build
:::

## Project

:::project{environment="node" template="nand2tetris-project4"}

### Objective

Write assembly programs for the Hack computer: a multiplication program and a screen-fill program.

### Requirements
1. Write Mult.asm: multiplies RAM[0] and RAM[1], stores result in RAM[2]
2. Write Fill.asm: fills the screen black when a key is pressed, white when released
3. Use only the Hack assembly instructions
4. Test using the CPU Emulator

### Hints
- Multiplication can be done by repeated addition
- Screen memory starts at address 16384 (SCREEN)
- Keyboard input is at address 24576 (KBD)
:::
